01:43.900 --> 01:45.800
Walter, hey, you looking for me?

01:47.100 --> 01:48.965
The Crazy Horse, that's you, right?

01:49.000 --> 01:52.200
- Yeah, you got something?
- Yeah, pole camera, three days ago.

01:56.300 --> 01:58.700
She locks up the club for the night.

02:01.500 --> 02:04.100
She's throwing away the garbage.

02:04.200 --> 02:06.400
Yeah?

02:11.200 --> 02:13.800
But then she changes her mind.

02:26.300 --> 02:28.100
Interesting.

02:28.600 --> 02:30.565
The good news is no polyps.

02:30.600 --> 02:32.300
The bad news is, as you can see,

02:32.400 --> 02:35.400
you've got a fairly severe case
of ulcerative colitis.

02:35.435 --> 02:37.800
- Jesus Christ.
- She was getting better.

02:37.835 --> 02:39.800
Then last week, another flare-up.

02:42.500 --> 02:44.850
How about the Prozac? Is it helping?

02:44.885 --> 02:47.165
She can't even sleep. Look at her.

02:47.200 --> 02:50.700
I'd like to start you on a regime
of Prednisone. It's a steroid.

02:50.735 --> 02:53.400
- Like for weightlifters?
- I've had great success

02:53.435 --> 02:55.400
treating this type of condition.

02:55.500 --> 02:58.600
I do need to warn you,
there are certain side effects.

02:58.635 --> 03:01.665
These are temporary,
but there's a chance of weight gain,

03:01.700 --> 03:05.700
accompanied by Cushing's Syndrome,
a swelling of the facial features.

03:05.800 --> 03:08.165
- Sort of a moon face.
- What?

03:08.200 --> 03:10.800
You've seen Jerry Lewis
in the last year or two?

03:10.900 --> 03:13.600
She's planning a wedding, for Christ's sake!

03:14.900 --> 03:18.165
It was fine one day,
then suddenly audio and no picture.

03:18.200 --> 03:22.200
- Somebody been fooling around with this?
- AJ had his friends over.

03:22.300 --> 03:24.300
How'd he do over there with your dad?

03:24.335 --> 03:26.200
- Raking the driveway?
- Fine.

03:26.300 --> 03:30.000
Except my mother kept asking him
if we were getting back together.

03:32.200 --> 03:35.300
You know, I dreamed
that I moved back in here.

03:39.900 --> 03:42.000
You know, just for the record...

03:44.000 --> 03:45.900
I realise what I did was wrong.

03:45.935 --> 03:47.700
My...

03:47.800 --> 03:50.065
activities while I lived here.

03:50.100 --> 03:52.600
Knowing you were wrong isn't the half of it.

03:52.635 --> 03:55.100
Oh, really? What's the other half?

03:55.200 --> 03:57.700
Well, suppose something
did happen where...

03:57.735 --> 04:00.165
theoretically, we did get back together.

04:00.200 --> 04:05.600
- Any marriage would need fidelity.
- Like Popeye says, "I am what I am. "

04:05.700 --> 04:07.750
Well, I didn't marry a cartoon.

04:07.785 --> 04:09.800
Well, it wouldn't be a cartoon.

04:11.300 --> 04:14.200
You had your own indiscretions yourself.

04:16.600 --> 04:20.200
- The thing with Furio?
- I did not sleep with him, Tony.

04:20.235 --> 04:23.000
I'm just saying that we're all human,
that's all.

04:28.800 --> 04:31.700
You know, the truth is, I got myself where I am.

04:31.735 --> 04:34.600
But your open indiscretion, total disregard...

04:35.300 --> 04:37.500
You're right, it was... it was horrible.

04:37.600 --> 04:40.000
A knot in your stomach when the phone rings.

04:40.100 --> 04:41.900
Like you were saying, you know.

04:42.000 --> 04:44.900
Theoretically though, if we do reconcile,

04:44.935 --> 04:47.200
that stuff will never happen again.

05:04.200 --> 05:07.800
- Come on, you gonna go or what?
- I was finishing my drink.

05:07.835 --> 05:09.000
Fuck!

05:27.000 --> 05:28.665
You can't stay holed up here.

05:28.700 --> 05:32.900
- That's not healthy, Carmine.
- How'd it get to this?

05:33.600 --> 05:35.800
Retaliation, counterattacks...

05:35.835 --> 05:38.000
We're at a fuckin' stagmire.

05:38.100 --> 05:41.500
We back down now, bunker down,

05:42.800 --> 05:45.165
what kind of a message does that send?

05:45.200 --> 05:50.000
Not just to Johnny's people, either.
Billy Leotardo. What the hell was that?

05:50.100 --> 05:53.100
This Blundetto asshole went off
the reservation.

05:57.200 --> 05:58.900
All due respect, Carmine,

05:59.000 --> 06:00.965
that's why you need to get out there,

06:01.000 --> 06:04.200
put your ear to the street,
let the guys see you take the reins.

06:05.300 --> 06:07.400
That's not how I wanna handle it.

06:21.000 --> 06:23.600
Hey, don't get me wrong,
I always liked your cousin,

06:23.700 --> 06:27.400
but whacking Phil's brother
was a major poke in the ass.

06:29.400 --> 06:32.900
You know my cousin almost cried
when I put him in charge of the casino?

06:33.000 --> 06:37.300
After all I did for that blue-eyed prick,
then he completely fucks me over.

06:38.900 --> 06:42.400
Now I practically gotta get
down on my knees to Johnny Sack.

06:43.800 --> 06:45.565
Where the fuck you been?

06:45.600 --> 06:50.200
Highway was jammed with broken heroes
on a last-chance power drive.

06:50.235 --> 06:53.600
Oh, you're gonna get fuckin' cute now.

06:54.400 --> 06:58.700
- Anything on Tony B?
- Nah, he's still on a milk carton.

06:59.600 --> 07:01.200
There she is.

07:01.300 --> 07:03.200
My Smelly Valentine.

07:03.300 --> 07:05.100
Christopher, that's not funny.

07:10.400 --> 07:12.200
What the fuck are you doing?

07:12.300 --> 07:14.500
I can handle a cocktail once in a while.

07:17.300 --> 07:19.265
You guys OK? You need anything else?

07:19.300 --> 07:22.300
- You're still feeling sick, hon?
- Please.

07:22.400 --> 07:25.500
They gotta replace her colon with a semi-colon.

07:26.300 --> 07:27.900
Maybe you should be a vegan.

07:28.400 --> 07:30.865
- Doctor says I gotta relax.
- From what?

07:30.900 --> 07:35.700
She's got the world at her feet,
she walks around like impending doom.

07:36.300 --> 07:38.400
Come on, we gotta go.

07:44.700 --> 07:46.700
Take it easy, now.

07:49.300 --> 07:52.900
Don't listen. People who've got
their health take it for granted.

07:53.000 --> 07:54.900
How's your thing with...?

07:55.000 --> 07:57.400
Just gotta keep an eye on it, that's all.

07:58.500 --> 08:01.900
So, Carm and me are getting back together,
maybe.

08:01.935 --> 08:04.865
That's great. The kids'll be thrilled.

08:04.900 --> 08:08.800
Yeah. When we get settled,
we'll have you guys over...

08:08.835 --> 08:10.800
Family dinner.

08:11.800 --> 08:13.500
Feel better, huh?

08:23.200 --> 08:24.900
John.

08:35.900 --> 08:42.299
First off, let me just say how sorry
I am for your loss. We all are.

08:42.400 --> 08:45.300
Take your fuckin' sorrys
and stick 'em in your ass.

08:45.335 --> 08:48.800
I could say nothing, be a heartless prick.

08:48.900 --> 08:52.000
He tried to talk, he couldn't
even say his last words.

08:53.800 --> 08:56.400
Anybody ever die in your arms,
you cocksucker?

08:56.435 --> 08:58.500
A family member, somebody you love?

08:58.535 --> 09:01.700
- No.
- Well, give it time.

09:01.800 --> 09:03.865
See if I can't make that happen for you.

09:03.900 --> 09:06.900
- That's enough.
- Philly, why don't you go have a drink?

09:06.935 --> 09:09.700
Don't tell me what to do, Jimmy.

09:10.400 --> 09:12.100
Jimmy's right.

09:13.200 --> 09:15.700
Fuck 'em, John. Fuck all of them!

09:24.200 --> 09:27.700
Was that fuckin' necessary?
He shouldn't even have been here.

09:27.735 --> 09:29.665
He's got a right to be here.

09:29.700 --> 09:32.600
He's got a right to a lot of things right now.

09:32.635 --> 09:35.500
My cousin acted alone. I did not sanction this.

09:35.535 --> 09:37.465
The lone-gunman theory.

09:37.500 --> 09:41.300
You know how close he and Angelo were
in the can. He flipped the fuck out!

09:41.400 --> 09:44.000
When he whacked Joey,
what flipped him out then?

09:44.100 --> 09:46.400
What do ya want, John?
What do ya want me to say?

09:46.500 --> 09:50.200
I want your cousin on a fucking spit!

09:51.700 --> 09:53.500
I don't know where he is.

09:54.500 --> 09:56.700
- Nobody does.
- Fine.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.200
Maybe one of your other relatives then.

10:01.300 --> 10:04.700
What, I gotta stand here
being threatened now?

10:04.800 --> 10:07.100
All right, nobody's making threats.

10:10.900 --> 10:13.165
Look, Tony's in hiding.

10:13.200 --> 10:17.400
You either deliver that prick to my door
or I will rain a shitstorm

10:17.435 --> 10:21.000
down on you and your family
like you have never fucking seen.

10:24.700 --> 10:26.400
We're done here.

10:46.900 --> 10:50.050
There are over 200,000 species of molluscs,

10:50.085 --> 10:53.200
and right there is a good example
of a conch,

10:53.300 --> 10:55.900
which is also known as a knobbed whelk.

10:55.935 --> 10:58.300
See, these raised spines...

11:00.100 --> 11:01.800
That's what I call my dick.

11:01.900 --> 11:04.100
I heard that.

11:04.800 --> 11:07.000
That's just nasty.

11:07.400 --> 11:09.800
Oh, fuck! Yo, check it!

11:09.835 --> 11:12.200
Oh, shit! Hurry up!

11:17.800 --> 11:20.265
Don't touch it!

11:20.300 --> 11:22.500
Apprentice Delaney, get back here!

11:31.600 --> 11:34.000
Little Meadow in a bridal gown.

11:35.000 --> 11:37.300
Couple more years, Grandma and Grandpa.

11:37.335 --> 11:39.500
Bite your tongue.

11:45.400 --> 11:48.300
So, the other day,
what you said, I processed it.

11:51.200 --> 11:53.100
You know, your feelings.

11:54.600 --> 11:58.300
It really hit home with me, finally.

12:02.800 --> 12:06.400
With you out of the house,
I've had a chance to do a lot of thinking.

12:06.500 --> 12:09.465
I mean, it's partly my fault

12:09.500 --> 12:12.400
but I need something else in my life.

12:12.500 --> 12:15.900
You know, with Meadow
getting engaged, AJ almost...

12:16.000 --> 12:18.100
You want another kid.

12:18.900 --> 12:20.600
No.

12:34.400 --> 12:37.200
It turns out there is a lot
for sale over on Crestview,

12:37.300 --> 12:39.165
a little over an acre.

12:39.200 --> 12:42.200
I was thinking I could build a spec house

12:42.800 --> 12:44.700
and take my dad in as a partner.

12:46.200 --> 12:49.200
I mean, my allowance is what it is, but...

12:51.400 --> 12:55.700
- How much is the lot?
- 600,000.

12:59.800 --> 13:02.600
Anyway, he would oversee the construction.

13:06.200 --> 13:08.700
Well, I'll call Ginsberg and...

13:10.000 --> 13:11.900
have him free up a down payment.

13:12.000 --> 13:14.000
And then?

13:15.400 --> 13:17.600
I'll move back in.

13:21.800 --> 13:26.400
Supposing that happened, what about
the other issues that were on the table?

13:26.500 --> 13:28.400
Well...

13:29.300 --> 13:31.365
I swear to you, on our children,

13:31.400 --> 13:38.400
that my midlife crisis problems will
no longer intrude on you any more.

14:00.400 --> 14:02.465
Are you having dinner?

14:02.500 --> 14:07.300
- Have you settled on a caterer yet?
- Can I talk to you?

14:17.800 --> 14:21.500
- You hear from Tony?
- I talked to Kelvin... Calvin... whatever.

14:21.600 --> 14:23.400
That redneck from North Carolina.

14:23.500 --> 14:25.900
The Bureau of Alcohol and Tobacco called.

14:26.000 --> 14:29.200
A bodega in Newark's selling
cigarettes without tax stamps.

14:29.235 --> 14:32.200
Stupid spics were supposed
to stamp 'em themselves.

14:32.235 --> 14:34.165
The feds are all over it now.

14:34.200 --> 14:36.600
I don't got enough on my fuckin' mind?

14:41.700 --> 14:45.500
- Any idea how you're gonna handle that?
- Handle what?

14:45.600 --> 14:48.400
Our cousin, you know, Phil and John.

14:48.435 --> 14:51.200
I don't know, I gotta think about it.

14:53.100 --> 14:57.400
From now on, Paulie supervises
the cigarette run. You split everything with him.

14:57.500 --> 14:59.300
- What?
- You fuckin' heard me.

14:59.400 --> 15:01.565
I got a fuckin' wedding to pay for.

15:01.600 --> 15:04.000
Well, if I were you, I'd cut out the open bar!

15:13.000 --> 15:16.000
Fuck this piece of shit.
I'm done! You hear me?

15:17.500 --> 15:20.400
Put my life on the line! My fuckin' life!

15:20.435 --> 15:22.500
Baby, I hate seeing you like this.

15:22.535 --> 15:23.965
Fuck family, fuck loyalty.

15:24.000 --> 15:27.050
You cost him a dime, you're a fuckin' pariah.

15:27.085 --> 15:30.100
I gave that fuck pieces of my soul, Adriana.

15:30.200 --> 15:32.300
You know what he said to me?

15:32.400 --> 15:35.300
- He said I should have a fuckin' drink!
- When?

15:35.335 --> 15:38.065
Up there, when we were up
at Uncle Pat's farm.

15:38.100 --> 15:41.500
You don't need to listen to him.
Isn't that why you have a sponsor?

15:41.600 --> 15:44.000
Him and Tony B, breaking my balls,

15:44.100 --> 15:46.300
teasing me like when I was little.

15:47.400 --> 15:50.300
What kind of fucked-up,
undermining shit is that

15:50.335 --> 15:52.900
to tell someone who's got the disease?

15:56.400 --> 16:00.500
You know I could take him out
in a second, that fat fuck. Bang!

16:00.600 --> 16:02.665
His kids wouldn't even give a shit.

16:02.700 --> 16:07.100
Don't talk like that. You're a better man
than he is, a better person.

16:07.200 --> 16:09.100
Fuck all this shit with Paulie.

16:09.200 --> 16:12.565
You know what hurts me worse,
right to my heart?

16:12.600 --> 16:16.400
Him and our ass-wipe cousin,
that two-faced cocksucker.

16:16.435 --> 16:20.200
He could get us all killed with New York
and him...

16:20.300 --> 16:24.100
Tony has to think about
what to do with him now, after all this shit!

16:25.500 --> 16:28.100
Me, he don't need to fuckin' think!

16:29.700 --> 16:31.300
Well, maybe I need to think!

16:32.100 --> 16:35.000
Ever thought of that, you fat fuckin' scumbag?

16:46.000 --> 16:48.100
That's the guy, Adriana.

16:48.800 --> 16:50.300
My uncle Tony.

16:52.500 --> 16:54.900
The guy I'm going to hell for.

16:59.900 --> 17:02.900
- Long Branch cops.
- What do you think?

17:03.000 --> 17:05.400
Not your average bulls... detectives.

17:06.900 --> 17:10.599
Call the Long Branch PD, find out what's up.

17:20.000 --> 17:21.964
So, you all set?

17:22.000 --> 17:25.099
- Don't look at me.
- Why? Ya look good!

17:25.200 --> 17:28.099
And you're gonna look nice
with the short hair.

17:28.200 --> 17:30.900
Like whatshername...

17:31.000 --> 17:34.665
- That actress.
- Just take me home.

17:34.700 --> 17:37.000
I can drop you off, but I really can't stay.

17:37.035 --> 17:38.900
Why not?

17:45.900 --> 17:49.800
All right, look. First off, like I said before,

17:49.900 --> 17:52.800
as far as all the medical bills
and the prescriptions,

17:52.835 --> 17:54.865
that's covered, ad nauseam.

17:54.900 --> 17:57.500
- You motherfucker.
- Hey, take it easy.

17:57.535 --> 18:00.465
This is how you leave me?

18:00.500 --> 18:03.600
I'm almost burned to death
cooking you a fucking snack?

18:03.700 --> 18:06.265
You could've been making yourself something.

18:06.300 --> 18:10.800
- Am I that fuckin' horrible now?
- No. You're not horrible at all.

18:12.900 --> 18:14.700
I'm going back to my wife.

18:14.735 --> 18:16.700
You selfish fuck.

18:19.700 --> 18:21.200
I hate you.

18:22.700 --> 18:26.200
There's just no future with us,
I told you that from the get-go.

18:26.300 --> 18:29.700
That's why I didn't want you hitching
your wagon to my star.

18:32.000 --> 18:34.400
You'll heal up. You'll meet somebody else.

18:34.500 --> 18:36.500
Fuck you!

18:39.100 --> 18:44.700
I didn't come here to fight, I came here to pick
you up and end this like a gentleman.

18:47.300 --> 18:49.300
I'm gonna fuckin' kill myself.

18:49.335 --> 18:51.200
I gotta take this.

18:59.800 --> 19:01.400
Is that you?

19:02.200 --> 19:05.800
I know you're there, just say something.
Where the fuck are...?

19:12.500 --> 19:14.800
Your call cannot be...

19:23.500 --> 19:25.600
- The Bing.
- Yeah, it's me.

19:25.700 --> 19:28.000
Have your friend at the phone company
call me.

19:28.100 --> 19:31.000
- Who, Gerard?
- I want to put traps on all my lines.

19:39.600 --> 19:41.100
Jesus. What?

19:41.200 --> 19:43.500
- We need to talk.
- I was buying medicine.

19:43.600 --> 19:46.100
- This way, please.
- But my car!

20:05.200 --> 20:06.600
Hello?

20:09.500 --> 20:11.400
Give me a hand, will you?

20:11.500 --> 20:14.300
I got more stuff in the car, so...

20:14.400 --> 20:18.100
- Where should I put it?
- In the bedroom.

20:19.400 --> 20:22.200
Oh, you made it.
Hey, I was just starting dinner.

20:22.300 --> 20:24.600
Yeah, it smells good.

20:29.700 --> 20:33.400
- What is this?
- I got you something small.

20:36.000 --> 20:38.400
Oh, this is beautiful!

20:39.500 --> 20:41.300
With my black coat.

20:43.000 --> 20:46.200
It's a HermÃ¨s. Supposed to be the best.

21:01.900 --> 21:04.600
