21:04.635 --> 21:06.200
This is all right.

21:12.200 --> 21:14.500
This is fuckin' weird.

21:15.600 --> 21:19.200
- AJ...
- No, he's right.

21:19.235 --> 21:21.600
It is fuckin' weird.

21:23.000 --> 21:26.600
You know what? We should celebrate.

21:30.500 --> 21:32.800
Here, give me your glass.

21:35.300 --> 21:38.300
The trick is, you gotta hold the cork,
don't let it fly out.

21:38.335 --> 21:40.500
Gab's uncle got a detached retina

21:40.600 --> 21:43.600
at his retirement party.
He never saw outta that eye again.

21:44.100 --> 21:46.100
That's festive.

21:48.600 --> 21:50.800
I wanna make a toast.

21:55.200 --> 21:57.200
To the people I love.

21:58.400 --> 22:00.300
Nothing else matters.

22:01.400 --> 22:03.700
Hear, hear.

22:09.600 --> 22:11.200
Slow down.

22:11.900 --> 22:13.900
You're supposed to savour it.

22:14.500 --> 22:16.100
It's important in life.

22:25.800 --> 22:27.765
- Open the door for Mr Mucklel
- What?

22:27.800 --> 22:31.400
- Open the door for Mr Muckle the blind man.
- Call 'em off my kumquatsl

22:31.500 --> 22:33.500
- What'd you say?
- Kumquatsl

22:40.800 --> 22:44.300
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
It's all right. It's all right.

22:45.300 --> 22:46.300
All right.

23:07.900 --> 23:11.000
- So?
- I was throwing the garbage out.

23:11.100 --> 23:16.400
So what? Isn't that illegal anyway,
to film people without telling 'em?

23:16.435 --> 23:20.000
And the reason you didn't just leave
the garbage in the dumpster?

23:20.035 --> 23:22.900
Bills and stuff.
Our account numbers were on it.

23:24.400 --> 23:27.300
- Friend of yours?
- Jesus Christ.

23:27.400 --> 23:29.365
His name is Gilbert Nieves.

23:29.400 --> 23:33.100
Partial traces of an infrared stamp
on his hand from The Crazy Horse.

23:33.200 --> 23:34.465
I don't know him.

23:34.500 --> 23:37.400
You told the police
that he was at the club that night.

23:37.435 --> 23:39.765
Let me ask you
a question, Miss La Cerva.

23:39.800 --> 23:43.800
Do you really think we don't know
what's in that garbage bag?

23:43.900 --> 23:45.465
He was stabbed in the club.

23:45.500 --> 23:47.650
You tried to dispose of the evidence.

23:47.685 --> 23:50.242
- I didn't do nothing.
- Miss La Cerva.

23:50.277 --> 23:52.738
I suggest in the strongest possible terms

23:52.773 --> 23:55.200
that you start telling us what you know.

24:06.500 --> 24:08.500
There's this guy, his name's Matush.

24:08.600 --> 24:13.100
He's a drug dealer.
He did it. I swear, not me.

24:13.900 --> 24:16.000
What's Matush's last name?

24:16.100 --> 24:21.400
I don't know. He's foreign, the Mid East
or something... Pakistan.

24:21.435 --> 24:25.267
Anyway, Christopher don't
let him deal in the club,

24:25.302 --> 24:29.100
but once in a while he'd sell me
some X or whatever.

24:32.300 --> 24:34.600
This is my friend Kamal.

24:35.600 --> 24:38.600
Listen, I need a favour.
We're trying to get an apartment.

24:38.700 --> 24:40.565
I gotta fax a copy of my passport.

24:40.600 --> 24:45.900
- You can't go to Kinko's?
- The guy's waiting. Two seconds, I swear.

24:47.300 --> 24:51.200
It's in the office, but hurry.
If Christopher sees you, he'll shit.

24:51.235 --> 24:53.100
That's for you.

25:08.700 --> 25:12.600
This guy was at the club, the dead guy,
but I never saw him before.

25:12.635 --> 25:14.665
