25:14.700 --> 25:17.800
but the guy said Matush
ripped him off, it was all laxative.

25:17.835 --> 25:19.800
Oh, boy.

25:21.400 --> 25:23.400
What's the number again?

25:24.400 --> 25:26.600
Hey, yo, you can't be back here, man.

25:26.700 --> 25:28.750
Cool out, yo! What are ya doing?

25:28.785 --> 25:30.742
- Give me my money.
- What?

25:30.777 --> 25:32.665
Don't get stupid in here.

25:32.700 --> 25:34.565
Fuck off, I got no beef with you.

25:34.600 --> 25:38.400
You still sell that beat shit, huh?
Fuckin' baby powder?

25:38.435 --> 25:40.400
- Look, I don't know...
- Get him!

25:40.500 --> 25:43.000
I'll kill you motherfuckers! I'll kill you!

26:22.300 --> 26:24.200
Oh, my God!

26:26.800 --> 26:30.300
We had to wait till later to get out
the mops and stuff,

26:30.335 --> 26:32.400
after we closed up.

26:32.500 --> 26:35.200
- If Christopher...
- Nobody has to know anything.

26:35.300 --> 26:38.700
- But you don't fuckin' understand!
- It's cool, OK?

26:38.735 --> 26:41.000
We'll take him out through the basement.

26:41.100 --> 26:43.100
Dump him in the ocean.

26:56.500 --> 26:59.065
Why'd you help this Matush?

26:59.100 --> 27:02.065
I wasn't helping him, I was afraid for myself.

27:02.100 --> 27:06.300
Besides, he's nice. I don't know.
I didn't wanna see him get into trouble.

27:06.335 --> 27:09.700
- Sounds like a real sweetheart.
- The guy was gonna stab him!

27:09.800 --> 27:13.250
He's not a bad person. He's very religious.

27:13.285 --> 27:16.700
- Religious?
- He prays, like, all the time.

27:16.800 --> 27:19.800
He went through a period
of rediscovering his religion.

27:19.835 --> 27:22.365
He don't even do drugs any more,
he just deals.

27:22.400 --> 27:25.800
Every month he sends all
his money home to his family.

27:25.835 --> 27:29.500
- In Pakistan?
- His brother runs a prep school.

27:29.600 --> 27:31.800
Some place for young boys.

27:33.200 --> 27:35.000
I was very impressed with that.

27:38.600 --> 27:41.565
He's buckled down.
He's much more serious as a person.

27:41.600 --> 27:45.765
- Does Christopher know what happened?
- No! Are you crazy?

27:45.800 --> 27:50.500
You're guilty of obstructing an ongoing
investigation into a drug-related homicide.

27:50.535 --> 27:52.600
You are looking at 25 years.

27:52.800 --> 27:55.865
- But I didn't do nothing.
- Take your head out of your ass.

27:55.900 --> 28:00.500
- You knew what you were doing.
- We can arrest you now, have you charged,

28:00.535 --> 28:03.100
send you over
to the women's house of detention.

28:03.135 --> 28:06.400
Or in the alternative you can cooperate.

28:06.435 --> 28:08.665
But I've been fuckin' cooperating!

28:08.700 --> 28:11.865
You've been giving us shit,
and I've had it!

28:11.900 --> 28:15.650
I want you wired up!
I want Tony Soprano on tape!

28:15.685 --> 28:19.400
- Your boyfriend too!
- No, I'm not doing it!

28:19.500 --> 28:21.200
Then you're all out of options!

28:25.000 --> 28:27.300
I wanna talk to my lawyer.

28:28.400 --> 28:30.365
Fine, who's your lawyer?

28:30.400 --> 28:32.765
I don't have an official one.

28:32.800 --> 28:37.700
- Maybe Christopher knows a good lawyer.
- Oh, you fuckin' piece of shit.

28:37.735 --> 28:41.000
I'll call the Public Defender,
they'll send someone down.

28:41.035 --> 28:44.700
Might take awhile, though,
this hour of the night.

28:55.700 --> 28:58.000
I think I left some shoes over there.

29:00.300 --> 29:03.200
I can iron these tomorrow.

29:03.300 --> 29:06.800
- What for? Send 'em to the cleaners.
- I kinda miss it actually.

29:06.900 --> 29:09.200
My wrist is getting weak.

29:11.600 --> 29:15.900
- I could help you there.
- Get outta here.

29:17.800 --> 29:21.500
No, let's give it some exercise.

29:21.535 --> 29:23.400
- What?
- Stop.

29:36.000 --> 29:41.000
Hi, it's Ade. Ma, if this is you, another gift
for the registry could be a decanter.

29:41.100 --> 29:43.800
It's me. Where are you?

29:53.000 --> 29:54.900
We may be doing it at our house.

29:55.000 --> 29:57.265
We've only got the one leaf for 16 people.

29:57.300 --> 30:01.300
Could you do a buffet? Maybe set a card table
up for the kids?

30:01.335 --> 30:04.300
It's our first holiday.
Ronnie wants us all together.

30:15.600 --> 30:19.200
Ade? It's been 40 minutes.
How long you gonna stay in there?

30:19.235 --> 30:21.665
How long will you let me go
without a lawyer?

30:21.700 --> 30:25.700
I told you, they're backed up.
We left four messages.

30:25.735 --> 30:28.500
Eight fuckin' hours I've been here already.

30:44.100 --> 30:48.400
- Jesus Christ, look at me.
- You want some coffee?

30:49.300 --> 30:51.200
I can't, my stomach.

30:53.000 --> 30:56.500
I wish you'd think about our offer.
It's not a bad deal.

30:57.300 --> 31:02.100
I won't wear a wire, I told you. It's bad enough
how I betrayed him already.

31:02.135 --> 31:05.500
It's not too late to have a future, Ade.
There are other options.

31:06.200 --> 31:08.700
Don't start with
the Witness Protection again.

31:08.735 --> 31:11.300
You love each other. You have your health.

31:11.335 --> 31:12.500
Yeah, right.

31:12.600 --> 31:16.400
Living like this
is what's costing you your insides.

31:18.900 --> 31:23.400
- I really need a cigarette.
- OK. Come on.

32:02.500 --> 32:06.800
There's no way she'll wear a wire,
but she might get Moltisanti to flip.

32:06.835 --> 32:09.000
- Why now?
- Problems with Tony.

32:09.100 --> 32:12.365
- Christopher hates him.
- That's confirmed by wiretaps.

32:12.400 --> 32:16.400
Cl12 mentioned it too. Something to do
with Tony Blundetto, the cousin.

32:16.500 --> 32:19.265
- What would Moltisanti want?
- I'm not sure.

32:19.300 --> 32:23.300
- He's got some interest in screenwriting.
- Put in a call to Sam Goldwyn.

32:23.335 --> 32:24.865
Promise her anything?

32:24.900 --> 32:29.700
Depending on what he's offering, maybe
immunity and relocation for the two of them.

32:34.900 --> 32:37.700
She's got to understand
that if she won't wear a wire,

32:37.800 --> 32:40.365
we can't offer her protection or surveillance.

32:40.400 --> 32:43.800
- I explained all that.
- She's got till 9am Monday

32:43.835 --> 32:47.200
to bring him in or we turn her over
to Long Branch PD.

32:51.500 --> 32:53.400
Tone, you got a call.

32:55.100 --> 32:57.000
Jimmy Petrille, Brooklyn.

32:59.500 --> 33:01.365
- Hello.
- It's me.

33:01.400 --> 33:04.500
That tennis match with those guys?
My guy won.

33:04.600 --> 33:06.600
- Oh, yeah?
- The other one, the son.

33:06.635 --> 33:08.767
- He dropped out.
- What, he got hurt?

33:08.802 --> 33:10.900
Nothing like that. Settled, that's all.

33:11.000 --> 33:12.800
All right.

33:16.200 --> 33:19.365
- Little Carmine's out.
- He's dead?

33:19.400 --> 33:22.400
Seems like him and Johnny worked out a deal.

33:22.500 --> 33:25.600
I knew he'd cave. He's a fuckin' pussy, that kid.

33:26.200 --> 33:28.865
Johnny Sack, boss of a family.

33:28.900 --> 33:32.300
Time was it would've been great
for us to have John as the boss.

33:32.400 --> 33:35.700
Smart as a fuckin' whip.
He used to be a pragmatist.

33:35.800 --> 33:38.765
Some people are better at being number twos.

33:38.800 --> 33:41.900
You thought John had an ego before?
Forget it now.

33:58.400 --> 34:01.065
- Did you sleep?
- A little.

34:01.100 --> 34:05.800
- So where the fuck you been?
- Christopher, we need to talk.

34:05.900 --> 34:09.300
- I asked you a question, Adriana.
- I know.

34:09.335 --> 34:11.400
There's something I need to tell you.

34:11.500 --> 34:14.199
- It's that fuckin' Bobby DeMarco?
- No!

34:14.300 --> 34:16.300
Please, Christopher.

34:18.600 --> 34:20.699
I gotta get through this.

34:25.500 --> 34:27.264
About a year ago...

34:27.300 --> 34:29.699
more maybe, I don't know...

34:31.400 --> 34:35.000
- I was arrested.
- For what? What are you talking about?

34:35.034 --> 34:38.500
- For drugs.
- Where, at the club?

34:40.300 --> 34:43.800
- You remember my friend Danielle?
- She set you up?

34:43.900 --> 34:46.500
She was an FBI agent, Christopher.

34:59.700 --> 35:03.100
She lied to me. They wanted
to arrest you too, Christopher.

35:03.200 --> 35:05.765
I was just trying to protect you.

35:05.800 --> 35:09.700
They said all they wanted was some
information and they would leave us alone.

35:09.800 --> 35:13.150
I didn't tell them nothing, I swear to God...

35:13.185 --> 35:16.500
Just licence plates, some other stupid shit.

35:16.600 --> 35:19.665
They wanted me to wear a wire,
but I wouldn't do it.

35:19.700 --> 35:25.900
But now there was a murder, Christopher,
and they know about it.

35:26.000 --> 35:29.800
At the club, Matush and some other guy.

35:30.800 --> 35:34.600
I tried to cover it up, but I had no choice.

35:34.635 --> 35:38.400
They've been filming us in the parking lot.

35:51.500 --> 35:53.965
We're dead, you know that?

35:54.000 --> 35:59.300
What did you do, huh?
How could you fuckin' do this to us?

36:05.100 --> 36:06.900
I fuckin' loved you!

36:15.800 --> 36:17.800
I'm sorry.

36:26.600 --> 36:28.600
My God!

36:36.900 --> 36:39.200
What are we gonna do?

36:49.700 --> 36:51.700
Careful here, my son.

37:05.600 --> 37:08.100
- Hello.
- T, it's me.

37:08.200 --> 37:10.300
You awake?

37:13.200 --> 37:14.800
I know you're mad, OK?

37:16.500 --> 37:19.100
I'm sorry.
When I heard about Angelo I just...

37:19.200 --> 37:21.200
Don't say it. Not on the phone.

37:21.235 --> 37:23.200
I know, I won't.

37:27.000 --> 37:29.600
- What should I do?
- I'll tell you what not to do.

37:29.700 --> 37:33.000
- That's come back around here.
- I know.

37:33.035 --> 37:36.000
I know, but... my kids, my boys.

37:36.100 --> 37:38.000
Don't worry. I'll look after them.

37:38.100 --> 37:41.100
Yeah, well, that's...
that's why I'm calling, to ask...

37:41.200 --> 37:43.700
Sure, why not?

37:44.700 --> 37:47.500
Anything else I can do for you?

37:47.600 --> 37:50.200
I don't know what to say, cuz.

37:50.300 --> 37:52.300
I'm leaving you with shit in your lap.

38:00.100 --> 38:02.800
- Hello?
- The night you went away,

38:02.835 --> 38:04.800
you know, 17 years ago,

38:04.900 --> 38:09.100
I told you that I got jumped
by a couple of shines.

38:10.900 --> 38:12.900
That's why I didn't show.

38:12.935 --> 38:14.800
It was all bullshit.

38:17.100 --> 38:19.465
I got in a fight with my mother and passed out.

38:19.500 --> 38:23.765
- What do you mean?
- I don't know. It was like a panic attack.

38:23.800 --> 38:28.800
I went down like a house of cards
and I cracked my fuckin' skull open.

38:28.835 --> 38:30.865
Why are you telling me all this?

38:30.900 --> 38:34.700
I felt guilty about it all these years,
like it was my fault you went away.

38:39.300 --> 38:41.465
Anyway, now we're even.

38:41.500 --> 38:44.800
So the casino, all that shit you did
for me is cos of that?

38:49.800 --> 38:53.200
You just take care of yourself, all right?

38:53.235 --> 38:55.100
You too.

39:11.700 --> 39:13.700
Hello?

39:13.800 --> 39:15.800
Gerard, it's me.

39:16.500 --> 39:20.700
- He just called.
- Give me a sec, I'll dump the line.

39:23.000 --> 39:25.765
- You got a pen?
- Yeah, yeah, go ahead.

39:25.800 --> 39:30.700
He's at Roy's. It's a business, Kinderhook,
New York. That's upstate.

39:32.500 --> 39:35.100
Yeah, I know where it is. Thanks.

39:50.000 --> 39:52.200
- Hello?
- Uncle Pat.

39:52.300 --> 39:56.100
- How's life at the old folks' home?
- I don't like the people here.

39:56.135 --> 39:59.900
- Do you know what time it is?
- I thought you were a night owl.

40:00.900 --> 40:04.000
Did I hear a rumour there was a problem
up there at the farm?

40:04.035 --> 40:07.465
The goddamn developer.
Some environmental crap.

40:07.500 --> 40:11.600
They can't start the demolition
without some special permit.

40:11.635 --> 40:14.200
And the house is sitting there empty,
damn it.

40:15.900 --> 40:18.500
Remember that... that time at Lake George,

40:18.535 --> 40:20.100
how you loved it?

40:20.200 --> 40:23.065
We could live someplace like that, maybe.

40:23.100 --> 40:27.200
- You could start writing again.
- I could do my memoirs, finally.

40:28.900 --> 40:31.700
And we'd have a fireplace like you like too.

40:32.900 --> 40:35.200
We could never come back here, Adriana.

40:35.300 --> 40:38.400
I don't wanna come back. I just want you.

40:38.500 --> 40:40.800
You couldn't even see your mother again.

40:47.400 --> 40:49.300
You want some eggs?

40:50.300 --> 40:52.300
I need to clear my head.

40:54.700 --> 40:57.800
- You didn't even sleep.
- This is a lot to process.

40:57.835 --> 41:01.400
I gotta think. I'll be back in a little while.

41:01.500 --> 41:02.765
Stay, wait.

41:02.800 --> 41:05.300
I'm gonna get cigarettes. I'll be right back.

41:05.400 --> 41:07.465
Smoke mine. Don't smoke.

41:07.500 --> 41:11.700
- Next you're gonna want a vodka.
- What? Come on.

41:13.500 --> 41:15.500
I love you, baby.

41:15.600 --> 41:17.600
I love you.

41:36.600 --> 41:38.100
Hello.

41:38.200 --> 41:41.100
- He wants to do it.
- Great, when are you coming in?

41:41.135 --> 41:43.600
A couple hours.
We'll get some things together.

41:43.700 --> 41:45.565
That's not what we said, Ade.

41:45.600 --> 41:49.000
Please, if I push him he'll say no.
I know how he is.

41:52.100 --> 41:55.000
I'm serious, Adriana. You've got till one o'clock.

43:00.400 --> 43:02.900
- Hello?
- Yeah, it's me.

43:03.900 --> 43:06.500
Look, everything's OK.

43:08.400 --> 43:11.300
Jesus, I don't even know how to say this.

43:12.700 --> 43:15.700
It's Christopher. He tried to commit suicide.

43:15.800 --> 43:18.600
- My God, is he all right?
- He's fine.

43:18.700 --> 43:21.650
He was up by Ramapo,
apparently he took some pills.

43:21.685 --> 43:24.600
A trooper found him in a bathroom of this diner.

43:24.635 --> 43:26.500
They brought him to the hospital.

43:26.600 --> 43:28.900
His mom's on her way up there now.

43:28.935 --> 43:31.217
Did he say anything to you?

43:31.252 --> 43:33.500
I mean, did he appear suicidal?

43:33.535 --> 43:35.700
- No.
- Are you sure?

43:36.600 --> 43:39.200
His mom said he's
very upset about something.

43:40.600 --> 43:42.965
Anyway, I'm on my way up there now.

43:43.000 --> 43:45.600
I'm gonna send Sil by to pick you up then, OK?

43:45.700 --> 43:48.100
- Jesus Christ.
- You know he's been drinking.

43:48.200 --> 43:51.100
He's probably fighting that heroin urge again.

43:51.800 --> 43:54.200
- Anyway, Sil's on his way.
- OK.

43:54.300 --> 43:57.600
All right. I'll see ya up there.

44:46.900 --> 44:50.500
I'd stop to eat, but I don't wanna
get to the hospital after Tony.

44:50.535 --> 44:52.500
I'm not hungry.

45:06.600 --> 45:10.000
They'll keep him a few days, maybe.

45:10.035 --> 45:13.100
Observation, do some tests,

45:13.200 --> 45:15.400
who knows?

45:41.000 --> 45:43.600
He's a strong kid.

45:44.400 --> 45:48.100
He's tough, very resilient.

46:02.500 --> 46:05.000
Why are you crying? He's gonna be fine.

46:44.900 --> 46:47.100
- No, please!
- Come on. Come on.

46:47.135 --> 46:49.300
- Where you fuckin' going?
- Please!

46:49.335 --> 46:52.100
Come on, come on! Fuckin' cunt!

46:52.200 --> 46:54.100
- Please! No.
- Come out of there.

